**IMPORTANT Announcement for Miners**

We will be releasing a new variant of the MultistepReasoning task. This variant will be additional to the standard MultistepReasoning task and will start off with a fairly small weight as a trial.

There are two parts to this task, the so-called "MultiStepReasoningGenerator" and the "MultiStepReasoningDiscriminator". The generator task will work exactly like the current task, just with a different scoring function.

The validator will generate a reference in exactly the same way as the current task and it is your job to match the validator reference as closely as possible.

Your response will the be forwarded to multiple other miners, which will then have to guess which response belongs to your and which is the reference generated by the validator. This is a 0-sum game, such that if the other miners correctly identify your response, you will get no points. If you manage to fool them, you will get the full score. That means your score will be calculated as a ratio of ```discriminators_fooled/discriminator_count```.

This means as a discriminator, you must train a classifier which can tell apart validator references from miner answers. This effectively creates an 'arms race' between generators and discriminators, effectively causing miners to score each other.

Due to game theoretic reasons this task will not be scored on a curve like the other ones, but you will simply be rewarded based on our average score.

(Anticipated) FAQs:

**Can a miner with multiple UIDs not just exploit this competition because they have the answers?**
No, they cannot. If a miners owns both discriminator as well as generator UIDs in the same task, since the game is 0-sum, they will always have an average score of 0.5 between their miners. The only 'benefit' they have is that they can choose which UID gets what ratio of their score.

**But even if my generator is perfect, by just random guessing I will only ever get a score of 0.5**
Yes, that's correct. The best-case scenario for generators is a score of 0.5, and vice-versa for discriminators the worst-case scenario is a score of 0.5. You will only be able to opt in to taking part in both tasks jointly, meaning that you cannot choose to only run a discriminator.

**When will this release?**
We have a draft implementation PR waiting to be merged into staging. This is not finalised yet (e.g. the joint reward pool from the above question isn't set up yet). We are still war-gaming this task internally to test/exploit-proof. The earliest possible release date will be Tuesday the 18th to give you ample time to prepare and train your classifier models.

Happy mining and if you have any question/concerns about this task feel free to discuss them!

PS: For those of you who are not familiar with the concept of a GAN (Generative Adversarial Network) I highly recommend reading up on it as that is effectively what we're creating here - just as Generative Adversarial Miners;)
